herdr_client — vendored into skill-herdr (herdr-claude-to-codex)
================================================================

This directory is a verbatim, unmodified copy of the `herdr_client` package
from the "herdr-python-client" project:

    https://github.com/54rt1n/herdr-python-client   (v0.4.11)
    Author:  Martin Bukowski
    License: Apache License 2.0  (see ./LICENSE)

It is vendored here so the skill is fully self-contained (no pip install
required). The library source files (__init__.py, client.py, transport.py,
exceptions.py) are UNMODIFIED from upstream. All adaptation/integration for
this skill lives in ../_core.py, which imports this package as its herdr
transport layer.

Changes from upstream (Apache-2.0 §4b):
  - tests/test_client.py: the `socket_path` fixture was changed to bind the
    fake server under a short /tmp directory instead of pytest's tmp_path,
    because macOS caps AF_UNIX paths at ~104 chars. Test-only; the library
    source is untouched.
  - tests/conftest.py: added so the vendored package is importable when the
    tests are run from this directory.

Upstream herdr (the daemon this client talks to):
    https://github.com/ogulcancelik/herdr

This NOTICE and the accompanying LICENSE are retained per Apache-2.0 §4.
